[X] VARIABLES & TYPES
    | Teach me Python variables and data types for DSA — cover int, float, string, bool, type(), type casting, and how Python stores values in memory with simple examples.

    [X] int
        | Teach me Python int data type for DSA — how integers work in memory, arithmetic operations (+, -, *, /, //, %, **), and where ints are used in algorithms like counters and indices.

    [X] float
        | Teach me Python float data type for DSA — floating point numbers, precision issues, math operations, and when to use float vs int in algorithm problems.

    [X] string
        | Teach me Python string data type for DSA — how strings are stored as character sequences, indexing, immutability, and why strings matter in DSA problems like palindromes and anagrams.

    [X] bool
        | Teach me Python bool data type for DSA — True and False values, how booleans work in conditions and loops, boolean operators (and, or, not), and their role in algorithm logic.

    [X] type()
        | Teach me the Python type() function for DSA — how to check variable types, why type checking matters when writing functions, and common type-related bugs in algorithm code.

    [X] type casting
        | Teach me Python type casting for DSA — converting between int(), float(), str(), bool(), when casting is needed in algorithm input handling, and common casting errors to avoid.

