[X] CONDITIONALS
    | Teach me Python conditionals (if, elif, else) for DSA — how decision-making works in code, comparison operators, nested conditions, and how conditionals are used inside searching and sorting algorithms.

    [X] if
        | Teach me the Python if statement for DSA — basic syntax, comparison operators (==, !=, >, <, >=, <=), and how if is used in algorithms for boundary checks and guards.

    [X] elif
        | Teach me Python elif for DSA — chaining multiple conditions, when to use elif vs multiple ifs, and how elif is used in categorization logic inside algorithms.

    [X] else
        | Teach me Python else for DSA — the default fallback in conditionals, how else pairs with if, and its role in algorithm edge case handling.

    [X] nested if
        | Teach me nested if statements in Python for DSA — writing conditions inside conditions, how to manage readability, and examples of nested ifs in search and graph algorithms.

    [X] ternary operator
        | Teach me Python ternary operator (one-line if-else) for DSA — syntax like value_if_true if condition else value_if_false, when to use it, and examples in array manipulation.

