    [ ] continue
        | Teach me Python continue statement for DSA — how continue skips the current iteration, examples in filtering arrays, and when continue helps simplify algorithm logic.

    [ ] pass
        | Teach me Python pass statement for DSA — what pass does (placeholder), when to use it in skeleton code, and its role when building algorithm templates.

    [ ] nested loops
        | Teach me nested loops in Python for DSA — loops inside loops, how they create O(n²) time complexity, examples in bubble sort and matrix traversal, and how to spot them in algorithm problems.

