[ ] STACK
    | Teach me stacks in Python for DSA — LIFO principle, push, pop, peek, isEmpty, implementing with a Python list, and real use cases like undo systems, balanced parentheses, and function call stacks.

    [ ] LIFO principle
        | Teach me the LIFO (Last In First Out) principle for DSA — what LIFO means, a real-world analogy (stack of plates), how LIFO shapes stack operations, and when LIFO behavior is needed in algorithms.

    [ ] push()
        | Teach me stack push operation in Python for DSA — adding an element to the top using list.append(), O(1) time complexity, and examples of pushing in parentheses matching and expression evaluation.

