    [ ] peek()
        | Teach me stack peek operation in Python for DSA — viewing the top element without removing it (stack[-1]), why peek is needed, and examples in next greater element problems.

    [ ] isEmpty()
        | Teach me how to check if a stack is empty in Python for DSA — using len(stack) == 0, why empty checks prevent pop errors, and where isEmpty is used in algorithm termination conditions.

    [ ] using list as stack
        | Teach me how to use a Python list as a stack for DSA — append() as push, pop() as pop, indexing as peek, why Python list is sufficient for most stack-based algorithm problems.

    [ ] use cases
        | Teach me stack use cases in DSA — balanced parentheses checking, next greater element, function call stack (recursion), undo/redo, expression evaluation, and browser history, with Python code for each.

