[ ] BIG-O NOTATION
    | Teach me Big-O notation for DSA — time complexity (O(1), O(n), O(n²), O(log n), O(n log n)), space complexity, best/worst/average case analysis, and how to calculate Big-O from Python algorithm code.

    [ ] O(1)
        | Teach me O(1) constant time complexity for DSA — operations that take the same time regardless of input size, examples (array access, dict lookup, push/pop on stack), and identifying O(1) in code.

    [ ] O(n)
        | Teach me O(n) linear time complexity for DSA — operations that grow proportionally with input size, examples (linear search, single for loop over n elements), and identifying O(n) in algorithm code.

    [ ] O(n²)
        | Teach me O(n²) quadratic time complexity for DSA — operations with nested loops over the same input, examples (bubble sort, checking all pairs), and why O(n²) becomes slow for large inputs.

    [ ] O(log n)
        | Teach me O(log n) logarithmic time complexity for DSA — operations that halve the problem each step, examples (binary search, BST operations), and why O(log n) is dramatically faster than O(n).

    [ ] O(n log n)
        | Teach me O(n log n) time complexity for DSA — operations combining linear work with logarithmic depth, examples (merge sort, quick sort average, heap sort), and why O(n log n) is the best comparison-based sort.

    [ ] best/worst/avg case
        | Teach me best, worst, and average case complexity for DSA — how the same algorithm performs differently on different inputs, examples with linear search and quick sort, and why worst case matters most.

    [ ] space complexity
        | Teach me space complexity for DSA — how much memory an algorithm uses relative to input size, O(1) in-place vs O(n) auxiliary space, and analyzing space in recursion call stacks and data structure usage.

